entries.meaning: The act or practice of importing again, or back to a place of origin; reimportation.
examples: It was these texts, translated yet again into Latin, which were the source of the reimport of swathes of lost Classical knowledge into Latin Europe in later centuries.

entries.meaning: A product which has been reimported.
examples: The low price of reimports has placed competitive pressure on local producers.

verbs.description: reimport (third-person singular simple present reimports, present participle reimporting, simple past and past participle reimported)

examples: We reimported the data in a different format.

entries.meaning: To import goods which have previously been exported, particularly pharmaceutical products, back into the country of origin.
examples: Reimported drugs may not be as safe as domestic products.
